{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":"2026-03-20T02:05:15Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"b0a625e44512d4fc9fad96076e770dd69c5fea4e3f8a4dbc3bdf3875350137de","created_at":"2026-03-13T08:15:31Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Dogs (alpha, bravo, charlie) repeatedly get plugin assignments (compactor-dog, dolt-archive, session-hygiene) written to .dog.json by the deacon, but the instructions never appear in the dog's mail or hook. Dogs start up, find empty hook + empty mail, and escalate to overseer. This causes a flood of HIGH escalations. Root cause likely in the deacon's plugin dispatch flow — it writes to .dog.json but doesn't send the corresponding mail or hook attachment.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"gs-413","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":null,"status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Dog dispatch: plugins assigned via .dog.json but instructions never delivered to mail/hook","updated_at":"2026-03-20T02:05:15Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":"mutex"}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"48e45f9d9ba9e0060f1f407313fca213b20a4b75931f0887aec4b0c596421aa7","created_at":"2026-03-19T03:24:56Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"When running gt dolt rebase on the hq database (72 commits), the rebase executes successfully but the post-rebase integrity check finds tables missing. Different tables disappear each run (wisp_labels on first attempt, wisps on second). The integrity check correctly rolls back, so no data loss occurs. Reproduces consistently with both --keep-recent=10 and --keep-recent=50. All other databases (2 commits each) pass preflight as too-few-commits. This appears to be a Dolt DOLT_REBASE bug where squashing commits drops tables that were created in the squashed range.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"gs-4bb","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"open","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"gt dolt rebase fails on hq: tables missing after squash","updated_at":"2026-03-19T03:24:56Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":null,"closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"894bf137f2e6178bd5bde64d1a33de87ce27797ea98699abe073e91f6f4b3015","created_at":"2026-03-11T03:32:23Z","created_by":"mayor","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"attached_molecule: gs-wisp-2qz3\nattached_formula: mol-polecat-work\nattached_at: 2026-03-11T03:32:43Z\ndispatched_by: mayor\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen a crew member's Claude process exits (context limit, crash, /exit, compaction),\nthe tmux pane goes dead and nothing brings it back. Every other agent type has a\nrestart mechanism:\n\n- Deacon: SetAutoRespawnHook (tmux pane-died hook)\n- Witness/Refinery: Daemon heartbeat loop\n- Polecats: Witness zombie detection\n- Crew: NOTHING\n\n## Root Cause\n\ncrew.Manager.Start() (internal/crew/manager.go) creates the session but never:\n1. Calls SetAutoRespawnHook() — no tmux-level respawn\n2. Registers for daemon heartbeat monitoring — daemon only scans witness/refinery\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd SetAutoRespawnHook() call in crew.Manager.Start() after session creation\n(after line ~846 in manager.go). This gives crew the same tmux pane-died\nauto-respawn that the deacon has.\n\nOptionally also add crew scanning to the daemon heartbeat loop for belt-and-suspenders.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"gs-4wy","is_template":0,"issue_type":"bug","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"70168+kingb@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":null,"status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Crew sessions have no respawn/restart mechanism — Claude exit = permanent death","updated_at":"2026-03-11T03:34:49Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":"mutex"}
